The paper focuses on the task of extracting event information from text, which is a common problem in natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a novel neural architecture to deal with noisy data, which is a common issue in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of factor graph constraints and belief propagation inference also suggests a focus on graphical models and probabilistic reasoning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests a focus on sequential data and time-series analysis, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
